# 1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)

# 🔹 What are Parliamentary Proceedings?

Parliamentary Proceedings are the formal activities conducted in Parliament during a session.

These include:

* Question Hour
* Zero Hour
* Motions
* Discussions
* Debates
* Voting
* Passing of Bills

📌 They ensure accountability of the Executive to Parliament.

---

# 🔵 Sessions of Parliament

The President summons Parliament.

There are usually three sessions:

### 1️⃣ Budget Session

(February–May)

Longest session.

---

### 2️⃣ Monsoon Session

(July–August)

---

### 3️⃣ Winter Session

(November–December)

📌 Gap between two sessions cannot exceed 6 months.

---

# 🔹 Question Hour

### First hour of a sitting.

MPs ask questions to Ministers.

Purpose:

👉 Hold government accountable.

---

### Types of Questions

#### Starred Question

* Requires oral answer.
* Supplementary questions allowed.

Marked by (*)

---

#### Unstarred Question

* Written answer.
* No supplementary questions.

---

#### Short Notice Question

Asked on urgent public matters.

---

# 🔴 Zero Hour

Starts immediately after Question Hour.

Not mentioned in Rules of Procedure.

Indian innovation.

Purpose:

👉 Raise urgent public issues.

📌 No prior notice required.

---

# 🔵 Motions in Parliament

A Motion is a formal proposal for discussion.

---

## Adjournment Motion

Purpose:

👉 Discuss urgent matter of public importance.

Effect:

* Interrupts normal business.
* Criticizes government indirectly.

---

## No-Confidence Motion

Moved in Lok Sabha.

Purpose:

👉 Test majority of Council of Ministers.

If passed:

Government must resign.

---

## Confidence Motion

Moved by Government.

Purpose:

👉 Prove majority support.

---

## Censure Motion

Specific criticism against government policy.

---

# 🔹 Calling Attention Motion

Allows MPs to draw attention of Minister towards urgent public matter.

Minister gives statement.

---

# 🔵 Privilege Motion

Moved when a Member feels parliamentary privileges are violated.

---

# 🔴 Half-an-Hour Discussion

Used when answer given during Question Hour needs further clarification.

---

# 🔹 Parliamentary Committees

Help Parliament function efficiently.

Types:

### Standing Committees

Permanent committees.

### Ad Hoc Committees

Temporary committees.

---

# 🔵 Importance of Parliamentary Devices

They:

* Ensure accountability
* Increase transparency
* Strengthen democracy
* Improve governance

---

# 🔹 Quick Revision Table

| Device               | Purpose                          |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Question Hour        | Ask Ministers questions          |
| Zero Hour            | Raise urgent issues              |
| Adjournment Motion   | Discuss urgent public matter     |
| No-Confidence Motion | Test majority                    |
| Calling Attention    | Ministerial response             |
| Privilege Motion     | Protect parliamentary privileges |

---

# 🔹 Important Facts

📌 Question Hour = First hour of sitting

📌 Zero Hour = Indian innovation

📌 No-Confidence Motion only in Lok Sabha

📌 Adjournment Motion interrupts normal business

